http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Pinarayi%E2%80%99s-march-to-focus-on-new-development-agenda/article13995204.ece

As the Communist Party of India (Marxist) [CPI(M)] is gearing up to face the upcoming Assembly elections, the proposed State-wide march led by party Polit Bureau member Pinarayi Vijayan to bolster party organisational set up will kick off from here on January 15.The ‘Nava Kerala March’ led by Mr. Vijayan will strive to draw the State’s developmental road map and will focus on the need to safeguard secularism.The march would be flagged off by former party general secretary Prakash Karat at the northern border town of Uppala at 3 p.m., CPI(M) district secretary K.P. Satheesh Chandran told a press conference here on Monday.The inaugural programme would be addressed by Leader of the Opposition V.S. Achuthanandan and CPI(M) State secretary Kodiyeri Balakrishnan, he said.Apart from Mr. Vijayan, party leaders M.V. Govindan, K.J. Thomas, M.B. Rajesh, P.K. Biju, P.A. Sampath, K.T. Jaleel, MLA, and P.K. Sainaba would accompany the march that culminates in Thiruvananthapuram on February 14.The march would be accorded public reception at 5 p.m. in Kasaragod on the inaugural day.Mr. Vijayan would address similar meetings at Chattamchal and Kanhangad on the same day, and at Kalikkadavu the next day before entering Kannur.